Use the standard library
This is how to fruit_distribution of s and n:
  Remember that digits is []
  Do this s's length times:
    Remember that ch is item count in s
    When ch is in "0123456789", then:
      Add digits to toint of ch
    End when
  End do
  Remember that total is sum of item 0 in digits and item 1 in digits
  The answer is diff of n and total
Now you know